{"title_page": "The Sergeant (1910 film)", "text_new": "{{Infobox film\n| name           = The Sergeant\n| image          = The Sergeant (1910).webm\n| image_size     = \n| caption        = \n| director       = [[Francis Boggs]]\n| producer       = Francis Boggs<br>[[William Nicholas Selig]]\n| writer         = [[Hobart Bosworth]]\n| starring       = Hobart Bosworth<br>[[Iva Shepard]]\n| music          = \n| cinematography = John Dored\n| editing        = \n| studio         = [[Selig Polyscope Company]]\n| distributor    = \n| released       = {{film date|1910|9|22}}\n| runtime        = One reel\n| country        = United States\n| language       = Silent\n| budget         = \n| gross          = \n}}\n'''''The Sergeant''''' is a 1910 Western silent film short directed and produced by [[Francis Boggs]] and written and starring [[Hobart Bosworth]]. It was shot on location in what was later to become [[Yosemite National Park]] in California.<ref name=Guardian>{{cite news |title=Lost John Ford movie unearthed in New Zealand |author=Ed Pilkington |newspaper=[[The Guardian]] |date=June 7, 2010 |url=https://www.theguardian.com/film/2010/jun/07/john-ford-movie-new-zealand}}</ref>\n\n''The Sergeant'' was part of a group of seventy-five early American films found in New Zealand in 2010.<ref name=Guardian/> The film was preserved by the [[Academy Film Archive]] in 2012.<ref>{{cite web|title=Preserved Projects|url=https://www.oscars.org/academy-film-archive/preserved-projects?title=&filmmaker=boggs&category=All&collection=All|website=Academy Film Archive}}</ref>\n\n==Cast==\n* Hobart Bosworth as Sergeant Robert Adams\n* [[Iva Shepard]] as Colonel Westley's Daughter\n* [[Tom Santschi]] as Soldier\n* [[Frank Clark (actor)|Frank Clark]] as Soldier\n* [[Art Acord]] as Indian Scout\n\n==References==\n{{reflist}}\n\n==External links==\n*{{IMDb title|1380196}}\n* [http://www.filmpreservation.org/preserved-films/screening-room/the-sergeant-1910 Clips from ''The Sergeant'' (1910)] at the [[National Film Preservation Foundation]]\n\n{{DEFAULTSORT:Sergeant, The}}\n[[Category:1910 films]]\n[[Category:American films]]\n[[Category:American silent short films]]\n[[Category:American Western (genre) films]]\n[[Category:Films shot in California]]\n[[Category:1910s Western (genre) films]]\n[[Category:Selig Polyscope Company films]]\n[[Category:American black-and-white films]]\n\n{{1910s-Western-film-stub}}\n", "text_old": "{{Infobox film\n| name           = The Sergeant\n| image          = The Sergeant (1910).webm\n| image_size     = \n| caption        = \n| director       = [[Francis Boggs]]\n| producer       = Francis Boggs<br>[[William Nicholas Selig]]\n| writer         = [[Hobart Bosworth]]\n| starring       = Hobart Bosworth<br>[[Iva Shepard]]\n| music          = \n| cinematography = John Dored\n| editing        = \n| studio         = [[Selig Polyscope Company]]\n| distributor    = \n| released       = {{film date|1910|9|22}}\n| runtime        = One reel\n| country        = United States\n| language       = Silent\n| budget         = \n| gross          = \n}}\n'''''The Sergeant''''' is a 1910 Western silent film short directed and produced by [[Francis Boggs]] and written and starring [[Hobart Bosworth]]. It was shot on location in what was later to become [[Yosemite National Park]] in California.<ref name=Guardian>{{cite news |title=Lost John Ford movie unearthed in New Zealand |author=Ed Pilkington |newspaper=[[The Guardian]] |date=June 7, 2010 |url=https://www.theguardian.com/film/2010/jun/07/john-ford-movie-new-zealand}}</ref>\n\n''The Sergeant'' was part of group of seventy-five early American films found in New Zealand in 2010.<ref name=Guardian/> The film was preserved by the [[Academy Film Archive]] in 2012.<ref>{{cite web|title=Preserved Projects|url=https://www.oscars.org/academy-film-archive/preserved-projects?title=&filmmaker=boggs&category=All&collection=All|website=Academy Film Archive}}</ref>\n\n==Cast==\n* Hobart Bosworth as Sergeant Robert Adams\n* [[Iva Shepard]] as Colonel Westley's Daughter\n* [[Tom Santschi]] as Soldier\n* [[Frank Clark (actor)|Frank Clark]] as Soldier\n* [[Art Acord]] as Indian Scout\n\n==References==\n{{reflist}}\n\n==External links==\n*{{IMDb title|1380196}}\n* [http://www.filmpreservation.org/preserved-films/screening-room/the-sergeant-1910 Clips from ''The Sergeant'' (1910)] at the [[National Film Preservation Foundation]]\n\n{{DEFAULTSORT:Sergeant, The}}\n[[Category:1910 films]]\n[[Category:American films]]\n[[Category:American silent short films]]\n[[Category:American Western (genre) films]]\n[[Category:Films shot in California]]\n[[Category:1910s Western (genre) films]]\n[[Category:Selig Polyscope Company films]]\n[[Category:American black-and-white films]]\n\n{{1910s-Western-film-stub}}\n", "name_user": "Quiksteppe", "label": "safe", "comment": "Grammar.", "url_page": "//en.wikipedia.org/wiki/The_Sergeant_(1910_film)"}
